statements: SELECT * FROM QuantumAnalysis;
SELECT measurement_name, measurement_value FROM QuantumAnalysis;
SELECT * FROM QuantumAnalysis ORDER BY measurement_value DESC;
SELECT * FROM QuantumAnalysis WHERE measurement_outcome='success';
SELECT measurement_name, measurement_outcome FROM QuantumAnalysis WHERE id=3;
SELECT * FROM QuantumAnalysis WHERE measurement_name = 'Bell Test' ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT measurement_name, measurement_outcome FROM QuantumAnalysis WHERE measurement_value > 0.5;
SELECT id, measurement_name, measurement_value FROM QuantumAnalysis WHERE measurement_outcome = 'Success' ORDER BY measurement_value ASC;
SELECT * FROM QuantumAnalysis WHERE measurement_outcome LIKE '%Failure%';
SELECT measurement_name, measurement_outcome, measurement_value FROM QuantumAnalysis WHERE measurement_value BETWEEN 0.2 AND 0.8 ORDER BY measurement_name ASC;
SELECT * FROM QuantumMeasurements;
SELECT measurement_name, measurement_value FROM QuantumMeasurements WHERE id = 1;
SELECT * FROM StatisticalAnalysis WHERE outcome = 'success';
SELECT id, analysis_result FROM StatisticalAnalysis ORDER BY analysis_result DESC;
SELECT measurement_name, measurement_value FROM QuantumMeasurements WHERE measurement_value < 0.5;
SELECT * FROM QuantumMeasurements WHERE measurement_value > 10 ORDER BY measurement_name DESC;
SELECT id, measurement_name, measurement_value FROM QuantumMeasurements WHERE measurement_value BETWEEN 5 AND 15 ORDER BY measurement_value ASC;

SELECT StatisticalAnalysis.outcome, QuantumMeasurements.measurement_name FROM StatisticalAnalysis JOIN QuantumMeasurements ON StatisticalAnalysis.measurement_id = QuantumMeasurements.id WHERE StatisticalAnalysis.analysis_result < 0.05;
SELECT AVG(measurement_value) AS avg_measurement_value FROM QuantumMeasurements;
SELECT measurement_name, COUNT(id) AS measurement_count FROM QuantumMeasurements GROUP BY measurement_name HAVING COUNT(id) > 1 ORDER BY measurement_count DESC;
SELECT * FROM quantum_measurements;
SELECT measurement_id, measurement_outcome FROM quantum_measurements WHERE quantum_system_id = 1;
SELECT system_name, system_type FROM quantum_systems ORDER BY quantum_system_id DESC;
SELECT * FROM statistical_analysis WHERE analysis_type = 'error';
SELECT measurement_id, measurement_time FROM quantum_measurements ORDER BY measurement_time ASC;
SELECT * FROM quantum_measurements WHERE quantum_system_id = 1 ORDER BY measurement_time DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT measurement_id, measurement_outcome FROM quantum_measurements WHERE quantum_system_id = 2 ORDER BY measurement_time ASC LIMIT 5;
SELECT * FROM quantum_systems WHERE system_type = 'Quantum Computer' AND system_name LIKE 'IBM%' ORDER BY quantum_system_id DESC;

SELECT s.system_name, qm.measurement_outcome, sa.analysis_type FROM quantum_systems s JOIN quantum_measurements qm ON s.quantum_system_id = qm.quantum_system_id JOIN statistical_analysis sa ON qm.measurement_id = sa.measurement_id WHERE qm.measurement_outcome = 'Success' ORDER BY sa.analysis_time DESC LIMIT 3;

SELECT qm.measurement_id, qm.measurement_outcome, sa.analysis_result FROM quantum_measurements qm LEFT JOIN statistical_analysis sa ON qm.measurement_id = sa.measurement_id WHERE sa.analysis_result IS NOT NULL AND sa.analysis_time > '2023-01-01';
SELECT * FROM quantum_measurements;
SELECT measurement_id, measurement_type, outcome FROM quantum_measurements WHERE measurement_value > 10;
SELECT analysis_name, analysis_type FROM statistical_analysis ORDER BY analysis_name DESC;
SELECT * FROM data_sources WHERE source_type = 'experimental';
SELECT researcher_name, researcher_department FROM researchers WHERE researcher_email LIKE '%@example.com%';
SELECT measurement_id, measurement_type FROM quantum_measurements WHERE measurement_type = 'qubit' ORDER BY measurement_id DESC;
SELECT AVG(measurement_value) AS avg_measurement_value FROM quantum_measurements WHERE measurement_type = 'photon';
SELECT * FROM statistical_analysis WHERE analysis_type = 'regression' AND analysis_result->>'accuracy' > '0.9';
SELECT researcher_name, researcher_department FROM researchers WHERE researcher_department LIKE '%physics%';
SELECT source_name, source_type, LENGTH(source_description) AS description_length FROM data_sources WHERE source_type = 'experiment' ORDER BY description_length DESC;
SELECT * FROM QuantumMeasurements;
SELECT measurement_time, outcome FROM QuantumMeasurements WHERE measurement_id = '123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000';
SELECT experiment_name, researcher_name FROM Experiments WHERE experiment_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM Researcher WHERE expertise_area = 'Quantum Computing';
SELECT analysis_name, analysis_type, analysis_result FROM StatisticalAnalysis;
SELECT * FROM QuantumMeasurements ORDER BY measurement_time DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT measurement_id, experiment_id, measurement_time FROM QuantumMeasurements WHERE outcome = 'success' AND measurement_time > '2022-01-01' ORDER BY measurement_time ASC LIMIT 5;

SELECT q.measurement_id, q.experiment_id, e.experiment_name, e.researcher_name FROM QuantumMeasurements q JOIN Experiments e ON q.experiment_id = e.experiment_id WHERE e.researcher_name = 'Alice' AND q.outcome = 'failure';
SELECT DISTINCT r.researcher_name, r.expertise_area, e.experiment_name FROM Researcher r JOIN Experiments e ON r.researcher_name = e.researcher_name;
SELECT s.analysis_id, s.analysis_name, a.analysis_date, a.outcome_success FROM StatisticalAnalysis s LEFT JOIN OutcomeAnalysis a ON s.analysis_id = a.analysis_id WHERE a.outcome_success = true;
